  "title": "Math Teacher",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:</p><p>1. Conduct Mathematics Classes: Deliver well-structured and interactive lessons to students according to the curriculum.</p><p>2. Assess and Monitor Student Progress: Regularly assess student understanding through quizzes, tests, and other assessment tools. Provide constructive feedback to students and parents on their progress.</p><p>3. Individualised Support: Offer additional support to students who may require extra assistance, ensuring that every student has the opportunity to succeed.</p><p>4. Maintain a Positive Learning Environment: Foster a positive and inclusive classroom atmosphere that encourages active participation, critical thinking, and a love for learning.</p><p>5. Collaborate with Parents and Colleagues: Maintain open communication with parents regarding student progress and collaborate with fellow educators to enhance teaching strategies.</p><p>6. Stay Updated on Educational Trends: Stay informed about the latest developments in Mathematics education.</p><p>We are looking for Teachers who:</p><ul><li>Loves working with children and making Math come alive</li><li>Is eager to grow professionally in a supportive, fast-paced team</li><li>Dreams of making a bigger impact in education and even running your own centre one day</li></ul><p>Qualifications:</p><p>1. Bachelor's degree in any field.</p><p>2. Prefer with teaching experience in mathematics, in a tutoring or learning center setting.</p><p>3. Strong knowledge of Mathematics MOE curriculum.</p><p>4. Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.</p><p>5. Passion for teaching and motivating students to excel.</p><p>6. Only Singaporean<br /></p><p>Salary: $4,000 - $6,000 per month</p><p>How to Apply:</p><p>Interested candidates should submit a resume indicating your current and expected salary to <a href=\"mailto:hello@supermath.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">hello@supermath.com.sg</a>. Please include \"Math Teacher Application\" in the subject line. Applications will be accepted until 28/02/2026.</p>",
